        Chart Review Except They're Not Anymore 04/10/24

        Yeah. I'm done with these reviews now. It was a nice 1 year, 3 months and 4 days while it lasted. Don't you assume I'll be vanishing from these pages anytime soon though, I'll still be posting my thoughts on the new entries and putting my rankings of the Top 40 in your faces for as long as I wish, but that is it for the in-depth and biased takes on what goes on in the music scene.

        Also college is quite literally assigning me to purgatory so that doesn't help.

        This also has nothing to do with the fact that Shed Seven have somehow achieved a 2nd No.1 album this year with a bunch of different renditions of their old stuff, and DEFINITELY not because they've stopped Bring Me The Horizon from romping to the top spot. Absolutely nothing to do with that robbery. Elsewhere Sabrina is still stuck at the summit, Nines has made a song that is better than it has any right to be, Addison Rae surges up the listings to give me a cavity, Linkin Park have ended up making In The End for the 212th time with their new one, and The Weeknd has clearly realised that in order to do bits these days, you've got to be BORING. And that is what Timeless delivers in spades. Also Kylie is done for again and Padam Padam was clearly a fluke. See you next week for the Coldplay fiasco.


        AMAZING TIER:

        Charli XCX [21] (Ah well it was fun while it lasted.), Chappell Roan [9], Linkin Park [14], Chase & Status ft. Stormzy [6], Shaboozey [24]

        GREAT TIER:

        Chappell Roan [2], The Weeknd [35], Linkin Park [18] (The League of Legends song for this year. If it worked for Imagine Dragons I guess...), Sabrina Carpenter [3]

        GOOD TIER:

        OK TIER:

        Sabrina Carpenter [5], Addison Rae [22] (I swear to heavens if the Live Lounge effect does what it did to Noah Kahan last year I'm gonna riot.), Gigi Perez [11], JADE [28], Sonny Fodera/Jazzy/D.O.D. [10], Billie Eilish [20], Teddy Swims [13]
